<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-501-544  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 501 544.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 7 1989 v6 n31 p50(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hughes unveils 386 servers, new net software. (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hughes LAN Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   LINC/PS/2 (Computer network software) (product introduction)Hughes Model 4450 (File server) (product introduction)Hughes Model 4460 (File server) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFile ServersSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The LAN Systems division of Hughes Aircraft Co. last week extended both thehardware and software ends of its product line by releasing six new 386servers and announcing a new version of its internetworking software suitethat now works with IBM PS/2s and a broader range of multivendor networkinghardware.andM;Hughes' new servers are based on a 25MHz 386 processor and feature suchoptions as built-in tape backup and dual hard drives.andM;Each unit is designed to run version 2.15 of Novell Inc.'s NetWare LANoperating system, according to K.C.andP;  Clawson, PC product line manager forHughes LAN Systems in Mountain View, Calif.andM;Augmenting Hughes' existing line of software that allows NetWare-based PCusers to access host-based networks -- such as those running TCP/IP, Novell'sIPX and Digital Equipment Corp.'s DECnet LAT protocols -- is the company'snew LINC/PS/2 software.andM;While Hughes' LINC/PC works only on PCs equipped with Hughes networkadapters, the new LINC/PS/2 software, due this month, will provide IBM PS/2swith the ability to call a set of protocols on the fly to access distant orhost-based networks.andM;The release of the LINC/PS/2 program also marks the first step in Hughes'plan to carry the LINC software to hardware from other vendors.andP;  WhileLINC/PC only supports workstations using Hughes LAN adapters, LINC/PS/2 willwork with Ethernet adapters from Hughes and Western Digital Corp., and withToken-Ring adapters from IBM.andP;  Hughes plans to add support for cards fromother vendors at a later date, according to Clawson.andM;LINC/PS/2 costs $95 per workstation.andP;  Server prices will start at $8,995 forthe Hughes Model 4450 configured with 4M bytes of RAM.andP;  The Model 4460,configured with 8M bytes of RAM and dual 327M-byte hard drives, costs$17,795, company officials said.andM;Hughes LAN Systems can be reached at (415) 966-7300.andO;</TEXT></DOC>